  "detailed_description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >A tool created <strong>by gamers, for gamers</strong>.<br><br>Because controlling your PC from the <strong>couch</strong> with your gamepad is <strong>priceless</strong>.<br><br><strong>Compatible with any controller!</strong><br><br><u>Coming soon:</u></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Linux and Mac support</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Customizable mapping<br> </p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>IMPORTANT! To avoid conflicts, we suggest disabling Steam Input. How? Very simple. In your Library, right-click the game, go to Properties, then Controller, and in the dropdown menu that appears, select Disable Steam Input.</strong></p>",
  "about_the_game": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >A tool created <strong>by gamers, for gamers</strong>.<br><br>Because controlling your PC from the <strong>couch</strong> with your gamepad is <strong>priceless</strong>.<br><br><strong>Compatible with any controller!</strong><br><br><u>Coming soon:</u></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Linux and Mac support</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Customizable mapping<br> </p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>IMPORTANT! To avoid conflicts, we suggest disabling Steam Input. How? Very simple. In your Library, right-click the game, go to Properties, then Controller, and in the dropdown menu that appears, select Disable Steam Input.</strong></p>",
